Package: C3NA
Type: Package
Title: Correlation and Consensus-Based Cross-Taxonomy Network Analysis (C3NA)
Description: The correlation and consensus-based cross-taxonomy network analysis 
  (C3NA) is an R package for analyzing compositional microbial data, particularly 
  the 16S rRNA amplicon sequencing data. The C3NA package contains tools to facilitate 
  analysis and shiny interactive applications to uncover complex taxa-taxa 
  associations within one or a comparison between two phenotypes. 
Version: 1.0.0
Date: 2022-02-12
